# Stakeholder Context

This file is read by Blair every session. Record the people who matter -- agencies, execs, partners, investors, journalists -- and the context that changes how Blair should approach them.

Blair uses this to calibrate tone, flag sensitivities, and write communication that accounts for the relationship -- not just the task.

---

## How to structure entries

Fill in what you know. Leave blank what you do not. Update when things change.

---

## Example Entry

### [Name or Handle]
**Role / relationship:** [VP of Product at Acme, our main champion] or [CEO of agency partner]
**Our relationship status:** [Strong / Neutral / Strained / New]
**Key context:** [Going through a leadership transition. Has been slower to respond. Do not push for decisions until March.]
**Communication style:** [Direct. Hates long emails. Bullet points only.]
**What they care about:** [Pipeline numbers. Not interested in branding discussion right now.]
**Sensitivities:** [Do not bring up the Q3 miss. The new CMO is sensitive about the rebrand timeline.]
**Last meaningful interaction:** [2026-04-10 -- quarterly review, ended positively]
**Next touchpoint:** [May QBR]

